# Firelands Core Mandates

- **Language:** English for communication, code, comments, commits, and branch names.
- **WoW nomenclature:** Use standard terms (`Aura`, `Unit`, `PowerType`, `SpellEffect`).
- **Reference:** Verify server logic and SQL against local clones `firelands-cata-ref/` or `firelands-core-ref/`.
- **Build tool:** Ninja only (`cmake -B build -G Ninja`, `ninja -C build`). Never use Make.
- **Compile policy:** NEVER compile automatically. Ask the user before building; compile only when authorized.
- **Delegation:** Multi-domain tasks MUST use sub-agents per `.agent/skills/Delegation/SKILL.md` (Auth, World, DB, Core).
- **Skills:** Read the matching skill in `.agent/skills/` before implementing non-trivial work.

| Task | Skill |
|------|-------|
| Features / repos | `Architecture/SKILL.md` |
| Business logic | `TDD/SKILL.md` |
| CMake / build | `Optimization/SKILL.md` |
| Cross-platform | `TechStack/SKILL.md` |

Operational details (build commands, deps, DB): see `AGENTS.md`.

## Cursor slash commands

- **`/auto-commit`** — grouped Conventional Commits (see `.cursor/commands/auto-commit.md`). Run when the user invokes `/auto-commit` or asks to auto-commit; do not push unless asked.
